	declare yyerror when using lalr.cc, as GCC 3.4.0 warns about the
	unused declaration.

	* tests/synclines.at (%union synch line): Put a dummy member in
	the union, because empty unions aren't allowed in C.  Caught
	by GCC 3.4.0.

